===Verb===
{{en-verb}}

# {{label|en|transitive}} To [[fill]] to excess.
#* '''1610''', ''[[s:The Tempest|The Tempest]]'', by [[w:William Shakespeare|Shakespeare]], act 3 scene 3
#*: You are three men of sin, whom Destiny,
#*: That [[hath]] to instrument this lower world
#*: And what is in't,—the '''never-surfeited''' sea
#*: Hath caused to [[belch]] up you;
# {{label|en|transitive}} To [[feed]] someone to excess.
#: ''She '''surfeited''' her children on sweets.''
# {{label|en|intransitive|reflexive}} To [[overeat]] or [[feed]] to excess.
#* '''1906''', O. Henry, ''[[s:The Furnished Room|The Furnished Room]]''
#*: To the door of this, the twelfth house whose bell he had rung, came a housekeeper who made him think of an unwholesome, '''surfeited''' worm that had eaten its nut to a hollow shell and now sought to fill the vacancy with edible lodgers.
# {{label|en|intransitive|reflexive}} To [[sicken]] from overindulgence.

